description.narrative:
The direct beneficiaries of this project are:
 At least 500 households producers (members of Passiflore cooperative) will benefit through the construction of storage shed, a contract to supply and improvement of transport through the acquisition of a vehicle;
 The members of the interprofessional body through a platform for discussion with the government, leaning experience platform and an access to price information by a price index to be established.

We will build upon the work the partners have already been doing and add some new business elements (input supply shops, packaging, cooling unit) to be explored and developed by Spark and implemented by local partners. Similarly, Caritas Burundi has taking up a concrete role in the value chain prior to Sparks involvement and focused on technical training, facilitating bulk buying of inputs and organizing Multi-Stakeholder Platform for the fruits chain. The enclosed proposal focuses on their strength and the activities they were doing in preceding years.


1. To upgrade the fruits value chain through targeted interventions across the value chain;
3. Prospect and establish new markets for fruits and fruits processed products of Burundi.

Strategic Obj.3: To increase the legitimacy of government authorities and enhance its role in economic and food security
1. To establish a multistakeholder platform (MSP) of the various actors in the chain;
